na of self-improvement. This study brings the discourse of enhancement into dialogue with the locus of healing in Calvin.  afunded by Schweizerischer Nationalfond (SNF)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aAnthropology. 0aChristian life. 0aSanctification. 4aAnthropologie. 4aEnhancement. 4aHeiligung. 4aJohannes Calvin. 7aRELIGION / Christian Theology / Systematic.2bisacsh  aEnhancement.  aJohannes Calvin.  aanthropology.  asanctification.2 aSchweizerischer Nationalfond (SNF)efunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2022z9783110994537oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831107469210 cprintz978311074593140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110746877zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110746877zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110746877/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGFb2022  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-GOA